Import peptide-spectrum matches

Source: R/readPSMs.R
readPSMs.Rd

Reads as set of mzId files containing PSMs and returns the PSMs as a DataFrame.

readPSMs(files, parser = c("mzR", "mzID"))

Arguments

files

A character of mzid files.
parser

character(1) defining the parser to be used to read the mzIdentML files. One of "mzR" (default) or "mzID".

Value

A DataFrame containing the PSMs stored in the mzId files.

Details

This function uses parsers provided by the mzR or mzID packages to read the mzIdentML data. See the vignette for some apparent differences in their outputs.

Author

Laurent Gatto

Examples

f <- msdata::ident(full.names = TRUE, pattern = "TMT")
basename(f)

#> [1] "TMT_Erwinia_1uLSike_Top10HCD_isol2_45stepped_60min_01-20141210.mzid"

## mzR parser (default)
readPSMs(f)
